INTRODUCTION
This Document is the Work Instruction (WI) for Audit Management
PURPOSE
This WI defines the steps that are followed to add, update and monitor the Audits
inside the organisation.
SCOPE
The WI applies to the QMSrs Tool set that accompanies this WI

AUDIT MANAGEMENT WORK INSTRUCTION
AUDIT MANAGEMENT PROCESS
This section displays the flow of the process.
CREATE AN AUDIT
This section explains how to create an Audit in the QMS.
To create an Audit:
Go to Audit Management section in the QMS.
Select Create an Audit.
Select the type of the audit (Internal, Supplier, Project...) from the drop down
list.
Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk * and any other fields you
have data for.
Click on save icon to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.

CREATE FINDING
This section explains how to add finding for an audit in the QMS.
To create finding for an audit:
Go to Audit Management section in the QMS.
Select Create Finding.
Click on search sign" " from the drop down list then select the audit that
you want to add finding for.
Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk * and any other fields you
have data for.
Click on save icon to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.
Finding Entry Fields
Below are the fields to be completed when adding finding.
Field Name
Description
Finding Details
Finding
Enter the title of the finding
Finding Type
Select the type of the finding from the drop down list or
add new type by clicking on add icon ' '
Additional Details
Enter the details of the finding

CREATE AN ACTION
This section explains how to create an action for an audit in the QMS.
To create an action for an Audit:
Go to Audit Management section in the QMS.
Select Create an Action.
Click on search sign" " from the drop down list then select the audit that
you want to add action for.
Click on "Search "button then select the finding that you want to add action
for.
Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk * and any other fields you
have data for.
Select ISO Clauses
Check the box beside the ISO Clause that appears
according to the finding type
Related Causes
Root Cause
Select the cause from the drop down list then click on
the title of the cause that appears on the left side of the
window , the fields will be filled automatically ,user can
also add ' ' and delete' 'sub root causes to the
main root cause or undo deleting " "

MANAGE ACTIONS
In this section the user can edit, delete and use the filter to search actions using
varying criteria.
EDIT AN ACTION
Go to Audit Management section in the QMS.
Select Manage Actions.
Select the audit year in which the audit occur from the drop down list to edit
its actions.
Click on edit icon beside the action that you want to edit (if the action is
still open).
Make the necessary changes.
Click on Save to save the amended data or Cancel to cancel the changes.
DELETE AN ACTION
Go to Audit Management section in the QMS.
Select Manage Actions.

VIEW ALL ACTIONS
In this section user can displays all the Audits actions with their status. Different
filter criteria can be used (Action, Actionee, organization unit ).
You can use varying criteria as follows:
Click on filter icon at the top of the window, then choose the search
criteria you want.
Select from the drop down list and click on next icon" ".
To clear the result of filtration click on delete Filter icon" ".
In this dynamic report, the user can choose the fields that he wants to appear in the
table by selecting from the drop down list of display fields that found at the top of
the page and then click on icon.

In this section user can displays all the Audits Records with their status.
